<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,655,680]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin participle “ 
<emphasis box="[642,749,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">destitutus</emphasis>
”, derived from the verb “ 
<emphasis box="[1040,1129,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">destituo</emphasis>
” meaning deserted, devoid of, or lacking, referring to the paucity of distinguishing features.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
